    "content": "This version IS correct and is from Daughtry himself. Even watch the video on youtube: \r\nhttp://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2E3-6ha6ySE\r\n\r\nCAPO 1\r\n\r\nIntro\r\nC#m     Am      Em      B#m\r\n\r\nVerse\r\nC#m                  Am                 Em\r\nI'm ten miles from town, and I just broke down\r\n                 B#m                      C#m\r\nSpitting out smoke on the side of the road\r\n              Am                          Em\r\nI'm out here alone, just trying to get home\r\nB#m                                        C \r\nTo tell you I was wrong, but you already know\r\n\r\n\r\nPre-Chorus\r\n           Am                      C\r\nBelieve me I won't stop for nothin'\r\nC            Am          B#m\r\nTo see you so I've started runnin'\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus\r\nAm          Em\r\nAll that I'm after\r\n B#m             C#m\r\nIs a life full of laughter\r\nAm             Em           B#m   B#m\r\nAs long as I'm laughing with you\r\n          Am            Em                B#m       C#m\r\nAnd I think that all that still matters is love ever after\r\nAm       B#m               C#m\r\nAfter the life we've been through\r\n         Am             B#m         C#m\r\n'Cause I know there's no life after you\r\n\r\n\r\nSMALL SOLO:\r\nAm      Em      B#m     B#m\r\n\r\n\r\nVerse\r\nC#m              Am                      Em                       \r\nThe last time we talked, the night that I walked\r\n             B#m                    C#m\r\nBurns like a light in the back of my mind\r\n              Am                   Em                 \r\nI must've been high, to say you and I\r\n                B#m                      C\r\nweren't meant to be and just wasting my time\r\n\r\n\r\nPre-Chorus\r\n           Am               C\r\nOh, why did I ever doubt you\r\nC            Am           B#m\r\nYou know, I will die here without you\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus\r\nAm          Em\r\nAll that I'm after\r\n B#m             C#m\r\nIs a life full of laughter\r\nAm     